  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Plumbing and Wash course Mikolongwe VTC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal Overview: to offer a quality WASH and Plumbing Technician course to young Malawians between 17 and 28 years old in a more conducive environment.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Plan:  In total 120 students would be trained over the three year period. Hostel accommodation required will be for 32 students at a time per year as DAPP is expecting the number of youth interested in this kind of training to be increased.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Summary:This project will benefit youth at the school to acquire new skills and knowledge in WASH and Plumbing techniques. The students/youth will also learn to establish and run successful WASH and Plumbing trade after graduating from the school. They can also get employed in the construction industry. These Technicians will be filling a niche in the technical requirements of the Construction and WASH industries in Malawi.  We envisage that the short courses will entice a significant number of practicing Plumbers who may want to upgrade their knowhow in water and borehole maintenance, apart from installation of domestic water systems. The students will also learn new techniques in the Sanitation field, such as different aspects of Pit- Latrine Construction and maintenance.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training of students, initially 120 students with about 50% girls.</narrative>
  </description>
